1270–1325":"1270–1325","1270–1336":"1270–1336","1220–1270":"1220–1270","1316":"1316","Abt 1240":"circa 1240","1336":"1336","1325":"1325","about 1270":"circa 1270","1320":"1320","1220":"1220","1240":"1240","1250":"1250","Abt 1270":"circa 1270","1270":"1270","Abt 1316":"circa 1316","Clan Fenton, East Lothian, Scotland":"Fenton Barns, Haddingtonshire, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Angus, Scotland":"Angus, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Airlie, Forfarshire, Scotland":"Airlie, Forfarshire, Schotland","Scotland":"Schotland","Airlie, Angus, Scotland":"Airlie, Angus, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"Abt 1240–Abt 1316":"about 1240–about 1316","1240–1316":"1240–1316","1250–1320":"1250–1320","1270–1325":"1270–1325","1270–1336":"1270–1336","1220–1270":"1220–1270","1316":"1316","Abt 1240":"about 1240","1336":"1336","1325":"1325","about 1270":"about 1270","1320":"1320","1220":"1220","1240":"1240","1250":"1250","Abt 1270":"about 1270","1270":"1270","Abt 1316":"about 1316","Clan Fenton, East Lothian, Scotland":"Fenton Barns, Haddingtonshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","Angus, Scotland":"Angus, Scotland, United Kingdom","Airlie, Forfarshire, Scotland":"Airlie, Forfarshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Airlie, Angus, Scotland":"Airlie, Angus, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Fenton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of various places, in Yorkshire, Lincolnshire, Northumberland, Staffordshire, and Nottinghamshire, so called from Old English <i>fenn</i> ‘marsh, fen’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘enclosure, settlement’.","Irish: English surname adopted by bearers of Gaelic <i>Ó Fionnachta</i> or <b>Ó Fiachna</b> ‘descendant of <i>Fiachna</i>’, an old personal name Anglicized as <b>Feighney</b> and sometimes mistranslated as   Hunt   (see   Fee   1 and   Finnerty  ).","Scottish: habitational name from Fenton in East Lothian."],"variants":[{"name":"Hunt","meanings":["English (southwestern): occupational name for a hunter, from Middle English <i>hunte</i> ‘hunter, huntsman’ (Old English <i>hunta</i>). The term was used not only of the hunting on horseback of game such as stags and wild boars, which in the Middle Ages was a pursuit restricted to the ranks of the nobility, but also to much humbler forms of pursuit such as bird catching and poaching for food. The word seems also to have been used as an Old English personal name and to have survived into the Middle Ages as an occasional personal name. Compare   Huntington   and   Huntley  .","Irish: adopted for various Irish surnames containing or thought to contain the Gaelic element <i>fiadhach</i> ‘hunt’; for example <b>Ó Fiaich</b> (see   Fee  ) and <b>Ó Fiachna</b> (see   Fenton  ).","Possibly an Americanized form of German   Hundt  ."]},{"name":"Fantom","meanings":["English: nickname from Middle English <i>fantom</i>, <i>fainton</i> ‘apparition, ghost’. There has been some confusion with   Fenton  ."]},{"name":"Finton","meanings":["English and Irish: variant of   Fenton  ."]},{"name":"Fenty","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Fenton  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Fenton was born about 1240, in Airlie, Angus, Scotland, United Kingdom, his father, John Fenton, was 22 and his mother, Mary Kettins, was 22. He had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Cecilia Bisset. He died about 1316, in his hometown, at the age of 78."},"et":{"Abt 1240–Abt 1316":"umbes 1240–umbes 1316","1240–1316":"1240–1316","1250–1320":"1250–1320","1270–1325":"1270–1325","1270–1336":"1270–1336","1220–1270":"1220–1270","1316":"1316","Abt 1240":"umbes 1240","1336":"1336","1325":"1325","about 1270":"umbes 1270","1320":"1320","1220":"1220","1240":"1240","1250":"1250","Abt 1270":"umbes 1270","1270":"1270","Abt 1316":"umbes 1316","Clan Fenton, East Lothian, Scotland":"Fenton Barns, Haddingtonshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Angus, Scotland":"Angus, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Airlie, Forfarshire, Scotland":"Airlie, Forfarshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Airlie, Angus, Scotland":"Airlie, Angus, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1240–Abt 1316":"noin 1240–noin 1316","1240–1316":"1240–1316","1250–1320":"1250–1320","1270–1325":"1270–1325","1270–1336":"1270–1336","1220–1270":"1220–1270","1316":"1316","Abt 1240":"noin 1240","1336":"1336","1325":"1325","about 1270":"noin 1270","1320":"1320","1220":"1220","1240":"1240","1250":"1250","Abt 1270":"noin 1270","1270":"1270","Abt 1316":"noin 1316","Clan Fenton, East Lothian, Scotland":"Fenton Barns, Haddingtonshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Angus, Scotland":"Angus, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Airlie, Forfarshire, Scotland":"Airlie, Forfarshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Airlie, Angus, Scotland":"Airlie, Angus, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1240–Abt 1316":"environ 1240–environ 1316","1240–1316":"1240–1316","1250–1320":"1250–1320","1270–1325":"1270–1325","1270–1336":"1270–1336","1220–1270":"1220–1270","1316":"1316","Abt 1240":"environ 1240","1336":"1336","1325":"1325","about 1270":"environ 1270","1320":"1320","1220":"1220","1240":"1240","1250":"1250","Abt 1270":"environ 1270","1270":"1270","Abt 1316":"environ 1316","Clan Fen